' Sequence diagram skeleton.
' Rename the diagram (after @startuml) and the file to match the scope.
' Theme fallback: replace `!theme plain` with these three lines if the
' user's PlantUML build doesn't ship the `plain` theme:
'   skinparam monochrome true
'   skinparam shadowing false
'   skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"

@startuml sequence-diagram
!theme plain

' Participants — declare explicitly, pick the type that matches the role.
' Available: actor, participant, boundary, control, entity, database, collections, queue
actor User
participant "Web App" as Web
participant API
control AuthService as Auth
database Users

' Optional: group participants when there are >5
' box "Frontend"
'     actor User
'     participant "Web App" as Web
' end box
' box "Backend"
'     participant API
'     control AuthService as Auth
' end box

' Optional: autonumber when there are 6+ messages
' autonumber

' Messages.
' Convention: -> for request (sync), --> for response (dashed), ->> for fire-and-forget.
User -> Web: action
Web -> API: request
API -> Auth: verify
Auth -> Users: query
Users --> Auth: row
Auth --> API: ok
API --> Web: response
Web --> User: result

' Optional control flow:
' alt happy path
'     ...
' else error case
'     ...
' end

' Optional notes — always anchor (left of / right of / over).
' note right of Auth: rate-limited

@enduml
